column6: “Catalina smile” crack around forward keel. Some gel coat damage in this area as well. Paint missing in various locations. Port aft waterline submerged.

Aft waterline remains submerged causing heavy growth on the gelcoat above the bottom paint. Recommend redistributing weight aboard, or raising waterline on the next haul-out. Paint is no longer effective. Missing paint is widespread, along with small blisters, most notable on the rudder.
